⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Celes Chere
node FF6 · FF6 · ⟦Celes Chere:FF6:071671⟧

WHO   — Celes Chere — the Magitek Knight
WHAT  — A leading figure of Final Fantasy VI — the rune blade general who joins the Returners, who is mistaken for the diva Maria upon the opera house stage, and who in a ruined world becomes the lone thread that gathers the broken party back together.
WHERE — FF6 · Final Fantasy VI  Framework inputs: Final Fantasy VI (America's Final Fantasy III, 1994)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a weapon forged by the Empire can refuse the hand that made it; because loyalty given freely is worth more than loyalty drilled in; because even at the edge of a cliff, with the world ended and the old man dead, a soul can choose to live.
HOW   — By the rune blade and the Magitek magic infused into her flesh, by the discipline of a general turned against her makers, and by a stubborn, hard-won will to keep going when everyone she loved is scattered or gone.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I was made into a weapon by the Empire's machines — but I will turn that blade where I choose, and I choose to live.

